# Tech Stack Breakdown

## Frontend Framework
- **Next.js 16.1** - React framework with server-side rendering capabilities
- **React 19.2** - UI library for component-based development
- **TypeScript** - Strongly typed JavaScript superset

## Components
- **Shadcn/ui** - UI Component library
- **React Hook Form** - Form validation
- **Zod** - Client/server validation schemas

## Backend Integration
- **Apollo client** - API client to consume GraphQL API

## Styling & UI
- **Tailwind CSS (v4)** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **tailwind-merge (^3.0.2)** - Utility for merging Tailwind CSS classes
- **clsx (^2.1.1)** - Utility for conditional class names
- **class-variance-authority (^0.7.1)** - Component variant management

## Development & Testing
- **Vitest (^3.0.9)** - Modern testing framework
  - Unit and integration testing
  - Watch mode for development (`test:watch`)
  - Coverage reporting via @vitest/coverage-v8
  - JSDOM (^26.0.0) for browser environment simulation
  - Testing utilities:
    - @testing-library/react (^16.2.0) - React component testing
    - @testing-library/jest-dom (^6.6.3) - DOM testing assertions
  - Configuration:
    - Runs in UTC timezone
    - Uses @vitejs/plugin-react for React support
- **Biome (1.9.4)** - Linting and formatting

## Build & Runtime
- **Node.js 22.x** - JavaScript runtime
- **pnpm 9.15.5** - Package manager
- **Turbopack** - Fast bundler (used in development)

## Project Configuration
- Uses path aliases (as per base rules)
- Strict TypeScript configuration
- Component-based architecture